post_text: Ufortunately we ended our season yesterday. Although we suffered our first defeat in the last 10 games, the coaches and parents couldn't be prouder of our young men. We played a very big and fast Waseca team and our SUPERLARKS didn't back down. Each time we had to come back and score we did. The one thing we've tried the get our kids to understand is you can always control your effort and they controlled it better than they ever have. In three seasons, playing much bigger schools these kids went 18-4!The future is very bright for our FB program and these kids will be a big part of it soon!! #PURPLEPRIDE

post_text: The SuperLarks continued their stellar season today as both the 6th grade and 5th grade teams shut out the visiting Byron Bears. The 6th grade dominated from start to finish and although 12-0 was the final score they were never in trouble and handed the Byron team their first loss of the season. The 5th grade clung to a 6-0 lead at half and then turned it up a notch in the second and also won 12-0. Both teams are now 3-0 on the season and will travel to Randoloh next week. Great job today Boys!!

post_text: The coaches have decided to have a season ending party Wednesday at 5pm for all tackle FB players grades 3-6 and their families. It will be held at Brad Skifter's shop right next to Olson Tree services on the west side of town. We'll provide the burgers and hot dogs for the players but please provide your food and drinks for additional family members. If you could bring a dish or dessert to pass that would be great. post_text:
For those of you that don't know this week's Homecoming game against G-E is a fundraiser for Tackle Cancer. This year we are doing something special for one of our own. As many of you know Carter Simonson was diagnosed with T-Cell Leukemia in Dec and he is in the middle of a very long battle. To help raise money for the Simonson family we will be AUCTIONING off a signed Superlarks jersey. We will also be running a raffle for a signed Superlarks helmet. Tickets will be sold at the tailgate party as well as during the game. They'll be $5 each or 5 for $20.

Carter will also be there as honorary captain!! He'll fit right in with his new Superlarks jersey!
